1. Wipe the Kubernetes Resources

First, remove the actual running applications and the namespaces.
 

# 1. Uninstall the Helm releases
helm uninstall prom-demo -n monitoring
helm uninstall my-app -n monitoring

# 2. Delete the namespaces (This cleans up all Pods, Services, and PVCs)
kubectl delete namespace monitoring
kubectl delete namespace techessay

# 3. Clean up the Custom Resource Definitions (CRDs) 
# The Prometheus stack leaves these behind; they must be removed for a "true" scratch start.
kubectl get crds | grep coreos.com | awk '{print $1}' | xargs kubectl delete crd

2. Clean the Helm Environment

Now, remove the repository links and the local registry credentials so you can demo the helm repo add and helm login steps.
 

# 1. Remove repositories
helm repo remove prometheus-community
helm repo remove bitnami

# 2. Clear the local Helm cache (removes downloaded .tgz files)
rm -rf ~/.cache/helm

# 3. Logout of GHCR and wipe registry credentials
helm registry logout ghcr.io
rm -f ~/.config/helm/registry/config.json

3. Clear Local Workspace Files

Delete the chart folders and packages you created so you can show the helm create and helm package commands again.
 

# Remove your custom app folder and the packaged tarball
rm -rf ~/techessay-app
rm -f techessay-app-0.1.0.tgz

# Optional: Clear any logs or temp files
rm -f *.log
